<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE BASKETBALL DAILY REPORT; AROUND THE NATION; MISSOURI GUARD O'LINEY 
ARRESTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Paul O'Liney, a key reserve at Missouri, was arrested early Tuesday for 
allegedly punching a woman in the face several times outside a nightclub. 
</P>
<P>
 Coach Norm Stewart said the guard, who is averaging 9.4 points a game, 
probably will be suspended for at least one game. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Oregon State Coach Jim Anderson was told about his future with the team, but 
the decision won't be revealed until today. Dutch Baughman, the athletic 
director, said he wanted to give Anderson a chance to talk to his players and 
family before making an announcement. 
</P>
<P>
 Anderson has a 70-72 record with the Beavers, but his only winning season was 
in 1990 when they were 22-7 and shared the Pac-10 championship. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Bernadette Locke-Mattox turned down a chance to be promoted to an associate 
basketball coach at Kentucky, Coach Rick Pitino said. 
</P>
<P>
 Locke-Mattox, an assistant, was offered the position after Billy Donovan was 
hired to coach at Marshall University last week. She has been on the Kentucky 
staff since June 1990. 
</P>
