</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Joe Garcia pitched a seven-hit shutout as La Quinta beat Woodbridge, 3-0, in 
the first game of a baseball doubleheader Tuesday at Woodbridge. 
</P>
<P>
 The Aztecs won the second game, 7-1. 
</P>
<P>
 Garcia is 1-0. Anibal Delacruz had a triple, Charlie Tuggle had two doubles 
and Corey Fox also had a double for La Quinta in the first game. 
</P>
<P>
 In the second game, Jim Livernois held Woodbridge to one run on four hits in 
six innings for La Quinta (5-2). Corey Fox had three hits, three runs scored 
and drove in two runs in the two games for the Aztecs. 
</P>
<P>
 In other nonleague games: 
</P>
<P>
 Katella 4-4, Foothill 1-2 -- Robby Erwin was two for two with a double and a 
triple and a run batted in in the first game, and Mike Stevenson struck out 10 
in five innings in the second game for Katella (4-3). 
</P>
<P>
 Servite 11, Valencia 5 -- Mike Sullivan had four hits and drove in two runs, 
and Erick Jekums had three hits, two runs scored and drove in two to lead 
Servite (4-1-1). 
</P>
<P>
