 Brea-Olinda 6, La Habra 2 (6, darkness) -- Marc Anspach hit his first home run 
of the season and Jason Theif had two hits and scored two runs to lead 
Brea-Olinda (6-0). 
</P>
<P>
 Garden Grove 7, Orange Lutheran 0 -- Ronnie Moreno pitched a five-hitter, 
striking out five, and had two hits and two RBIs for visiting Garden Grove 
(4-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Huntington Beach 8, Century 0 -- Craig Daedelow hit a three-run home run in 
the fourth inning for Huntington Beach (5-1). Jim Brewer (2-0) pitched four 
shutout innings to earn the victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Bolsa Grande 3, Downey Warren 1 -- Bryan Moore pitched a five-hitter with 
three strikeouts for host Bolsa Grande (2-2). Glen Strzelecki had two hits, 
including a triple, scored a run and drove in another for Bolsa Grande. 
</P>
<P>
 Kennedy 5, Western 0 -- Chris Clark had two hits and an RBI and three pitchers 
combined to get the shutout for Kennedy (4-2). 
</P>
