<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: BANKING & FINANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fannie Mae to Reach Out to Potential Home Buyers: The nation's largest home 
mortgage investor said it plans to help finance homes for 10 million families 
in "communities in need," reaching out first to minorities and people who are 
now renting.The Federal National Mortgage Assn. said it expects to put $1 
trillion into the effort by the close of the decade. Since its inception in 
1938, Fannie Mae has provided about $1.35 trillion in home financing. The plan 
will also serve families with incomes at or below the median for their 
communities, new immigrants, residents of central cities and other underserved 
areas. 
</P>
