<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: AUTOS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Strike Threatens Production at GM Assembly Plants: Negotiators for General 
Motors Corp. and unionized workers at two brake plants resumed contract talks, 
seeking to end a strike that could soon shut down at least two GM assembly 
plants.Three thousand members of United Auto Workers Local 696 in Dayton, Ohio, 
walked off the job Monday after negotiators failed to agree on a new three-year 
contract. Joe Hasenjager, president of the local, has said the issues 
separating the two sides include job security and subcontracting. GM officials 
say production at the company's Saturn plant in Spring Hill, Tenn., and its 
truck plant in Janesville, Wis., will have to stop if the strike is not 
resolved by today. 
</P>
