<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ATHLETES OF THE WEEK: ERICKSON DUMAUAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fullerton, So. 
</P>
<P>
 Baseball / Left field 
</P>
<P>
 Dumaual, from Esperanza High, picked up the nickname "Twilight" because of his 
recent exploits. According to Dave Schechter, sports information director, 
Dumaual is "in a zone."Dumaual was seven for eight and Fullerton won both its 
games last week. He had three doubles, drove in three runs, scored five runs 
and had a stolen base. Dumaual started the week hitting .609 (14 for 23) in 
Orange Empire Conference play and leading the team with 19 runs scored. He was 
hitting .421 (24 for 57) overall in the Hornets' first 18 games. Other 
notables: 
</P>
<P>
 * Rob Crabtree, Cypress, pitched a four-hitter with 13 strikeouts to beat 
Rancho Santiago, 5-2, and stop the Dons' 12-game winning streak. 
</P>
<P>
 * Jerome Valentin, Saddleback, shot a two-under 69 at Rancho Park golf course 
in Los Angeles to help the Gauchos to a nonconference victory. 
</P>
</TEXT>
