<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ATHLETES OF THE WEEK: FIONA JONES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Orange Coast, So. 
</P>
<P>
 Tennis 
</P>
<P>
 Jones showed her ability to win quickly as well as her ability to win a 
marathon match for the Orange Coast team.Jones, from Dana Hills High, had 
little trouble in her Orange Empire Conference singles matches. She beat Stacie 
Meeks of Golden West, 6-1, 6-1, then rolled past Debby Springer of Fullerton, 
6-0, 6-3. But Jones, ranked eighth in the state, needed three hours 45 minutes 
to beat Grossmont's Julie Dobrin, 5-7, 6-4, 7-6 (8-6). Dobrin is ranked 10th in 
the state. Orange Coast, second-ranked in the state, beat top-ranked Grossmont, 
7-1. Other notables: 
</P>
<P>
 * Michelle Morris, Rancho Santiago, set records in the 200 individual medley, 
the 200 freestyle and the 100 butterfly as the Dons beat Grossmont. 
</P>
<P>
 * Emilie Pavlovich, Saddleback, won the 50 freestyle at the Mt. San Antonio 
Invitational and helped the Gauchos to a second-place finish. 
</P>
</TEXT>
