<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP NOTES: WHITTIER CHRISTIAN'S HERRON TO STEP DOWN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dave Herron, Whittier Christian boys' volleyball coach, will retire at the end 
of the season, he said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Herron accepted a job to coach men's and women's volleyball at Northland 
Baptist Bible, a National Christian College Athletic Assn. school in Dunbar, 
Wis. 
</P>
<P>
 Herron has coached eight seasons at Whittier Christian and led the Heralds to 
their third consecutive Southern Section championship last season. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 El Dorado softball pitcher Heather Hamer has orally committed to attend 
Kansas, her father said. 
</P>
<P>
 Hamer, whose earned-run average over her three-year varsity career is less 
than 1.00, chose the Jayhawks over Akron and St. Peters of New Jersey. 
</P>
<P>
 She pitched a no-hitter Tuesday against La Habra in a 5-0 victory; she faced 
the minimum 21 batters. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The Pacifica boys' basketball team will conduct a scrimmage and auction today 
at the school to help raise funds for its trip to the State Division III 
championship game. 
</P>
<P>
 The Mariners will play Sacramento Foothill on Saturday at the Oakland Coliseum 
Arena. 
</P>
<P>
 The team will scrimmage beginning at 7:30 p.m. There also will be a silent 
auction of team memorabilia and a few odd items. 
</P>
<P>
 Among the items will be the jersey of senior forward Chris Vlasic and the 
shoes of senior forward Jon Surface. Also available will be locks of hair from 
junior guard Jimmy Agatep. 
</P>
<P>
 Admission is $4 for adults and $2 for children younger than 12. MICHAEL 
ITAGAKI 
</P>
</TEXT>
