<HEADLINE>
<P>
PALMER INVITES WOODS TO PLAY IN TOUR EVENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARTIN BECK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tiger Woods is absent from the Western High golf team this week, but he has a 
good excuse: a note from Arnold Palmer. 
</P>
<P>
 Woods accepted a personal invitation from Palmer to play in the Nestle 
Invitational in Orlando, Fla.The PGA Tour event starts Thursday at Bay Hill, 
which Palmer owns. 
</P>
<P>
 It will be Woods' fifth PGA event and sixth major professional tournament. 
Last month, he made the cut for the first time in a pro event, at the Johnnie 
Walker Classic in Phuket, Thailand. Woods finished eight-over-par 292 in the 
four-day tournament, 15 strokes behind winner Greg Norman. 
</P>
<P>
 Western Coach Don Crosby said Woods' absence won't hurt the team because the 
league season hasn't started. 
</P>
<P>
 "He missed one week last year," Crosby said, "and one this year, which is no 
big deal because he'll come back next week fired up." MARTIN BECK 
</P>
</TEXT>
