</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two Cubans fleeing their island's economic troubles jumped ship at the Panama 
Canal on Tuesday and were granted temporary refugee status by the Panamanian 
government, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The men were on a boat taking sugar from Cuba to North Korea. 
</P>
<P>
