<HEADLINE>
<P>
TV RATINGS; ABC PLACES 6 SHOWS IN TOP 10, INCLUDING 2 NEW SERIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LEE MARGULIES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 With six shows in the Top 10--including the debuts of two series--ABC won the 
prime-time ratings race last week, the A.C. Nielsen Co. reported Tuesday. It 
was the 10th time ABC has won this season, but the network still trails CBS in 
the season-to-date standings. 
</P>
<P>
 "Home Improvement," "Roseanne" and "Grace Under Fire" gave ABC a 1-2-3 punch 
at the top of the list, followed by "Coach" (No. 6) and the premieres of the 
newsmagazine "Turning Point" (No. 8) and the comedy "Thunder Alley" (No. 10), 
with Ed Asner and Diane Venora. 
</P>
<P>
 "Thunder Alley" was pitted against the second installment of CBS' "Tom," which 
finished 70th among the week's 94 prime-time network programs. CBS fared far 
better with "The Road Home," which in its second outing won the 8 p.m. Saturday 
time slot. 
</P>
<P>
 Not so fortunate was NBC's "Winnetka Road," which premiered at 10 p.m. 
Saturday and tied at No. 75, attracting 14% of the available viewers. Southland 
Ratings 
</P>
