<HEADLINE>
<P>
RAMS OFFER: $4.1 MILLION TO DONNALLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By T.J. SIMERS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After making a favorable impression with Oiler wide receiver Haywood Jeffires 
on Tuesday, the Rams continued their raid on Houston Oiler personnel and 
presented offensive tackle Kevin Donnalley with a $4.1-million, four-year offer 
sheet. 
</P>
<P>
 "I'm going to sign it (today) and then wait and see if Houston will match it," 
Donnalley said. "I'd rather play in L.A. . . . I just hope Houston doesn't 
match the offer." 
</P>
<P>
 The Rams declined to reveal the yearly breakdown, but it has been learned that 
they have offered him a $1-million signing bonus and salaries of $700,000 in 
1994 and '95, $800,000 in '96 and $900,000 in '97. Donnalley earned $275,000 in 
1993. T.J. SIMERS 
</P>
</TEXT>
