<P>
 SAVE THE KIDS: Dear parents: There is hope for children losing brain cells by 
watching too much TV. They can still lead normal lives. . . . Schools, like 
Harvard-Westlake in Studio City, teach media literacy, showing children how to 
manipulate the screen images instead of vice versa."It's not the quality of the 
TV that matters," said one educator. "It's the quality of the skills of the 
person who uses the TV." (E1) 
</P>
<P>
 SPRINGTIME: Baseball isn't the only rite associated with spring. This is also 
the season of wildflower viewing, and once again, the Theodore Payne Foundation 
in Sun Valley is sponsoring a 24-hour Wildflower Hotline ((818) 768-3533) 
through May 26 with a four-minute recording listing popular spots. . . . Last 
year, the line received 18,000 calls. 
</P>
