 QUICK EXIT: Maybe it was the unfamiliar Oklahoma climate. Or maybe the team 
wanted to hurry home to watch the NCAA Tournament. Whatever the case, The 
Master's College in Newhall (above) quickly bowed out Tuesday of the NAIA 
Division I tournament in Tulsa, losing 98-85 to Georgia Southwestern. . . . 
Still, Master's (28-5) had a great year. (C10) 
</P>
