<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; NEW SUBSTATION FOR POLICE IS VANDALIZED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Vandals took aim at Ventura's first storefront police station early Tuesday, 
lobbing a rock through a window weeks before the drop-in center is scheduled to 
open, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Sgt. Carl Handy said he believed that the window was smashed by youths living 
near the new substation at 6368 Bristol Road in Montalvo.No arrests have been 
made. 
</P>
<P>
 "As far as I'm concerned, it was directly pointed at us," he said. "On the 
other hand, it won't make a lick of difference, because we're going to come in 
no matter what." 
</P>
<P>
 Department officials said they hope to open the small storefront, squeezed 
between a video store and a Laundromat, by the end of the month. It will be 
open a few hours a day and used as a base station for two officers patrolling 
the Montalvo area. 
</P>
<P>
 The storefront is patterned on two similar substations in Oxnard, one of which 
was firebombed before it opened. JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</TEXT>
