<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OJAI VALLEY; FORUM SET TO DISCUSS AREA'S TRANSIT 
NEEDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A community meeting is scheduled tonight in Meiners Oaks to discuss transit 
needs for residents of the Ojai Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 Supervisor Susan K. Lacey and the Ventura County Transportation Commission are 
seeking input from residents about what kind of public transit services should 
be offered and whether there is support for extending the Ojai trolley beyond 
city limits. 
</P>
<P>
 Officials at South Coast Area Transit recently decided to cancel the express 
route that runs from the Ojai Valley to Ventura and Oxnard. That cancellation 
becomes effective in July. 
</P>
<P>
 Although SCAT will continue to offer its regular route through the valley, 
Lacey and commission officials want to see whether bus service should be 
extended through Meiners Oaks and other areas. 
</P>
<P>
 The two-hour forum is scheduled at 7 p.m. at Meiners Oaks School, 400 S. 
Lomita Ave. JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</TEXT>
