<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: PORT HUENEME; POLICE INVESTIGATE DRIVE-BY SHOOTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Port Hueneme police are investigating a drive-by shooting in which several 
rounds were fired into an occupied apartment, authorities said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 No one was injured in the incident, which occurred about 5:35 p.m. Monday in 
the 400 block of East Clara Street.Witnesses told police that they saw a red 
car speed away after the shots were fired, said Sgt. Jerry Beck. 
</P>
<P>
 Several bullets passed through the apartment's exterior wall into the kitchen 
and one of the bedrooms. The occupants, Bryan Davies, 29, and Paul Mitchell, 
22, were sitting on the living room floor watching TV, Beck said. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators said they do not believe that the attack was gang-related. 
Davies told police that he believes that the shooting was directed at him, Beck 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators have identified a suspect, but no arrests have been made, police 
said. JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</TEXT>
