<P>
EAST: THOUSAND OAKS; THRIFT STORE AIDS CONEJO SYMPHONY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEPHANIE SIMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Women looking for discount fashion can buy secondhand clothes and support the 
Conejo Symphony at the same time during a fund-raiser running through May to 
support the orchestra. 
</P>
<P>
 Hoping to raise $20,000, the Symphony Guild has set up a thrift store in the 
Westlake Plaza shopping center, at 1018 Westlake Blvd.The shop, called 
Secondhand Rose, sells donated women's clothing, and is open Monday through 
Saturday from 11 a.m. to 6 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Organizers have set an ambitious fund-raising target because the symphony 
orchestra needs money to prepare concerts for the Civic Arts Plaza's inaugural 
season, which starts next fall. 
</P>
<P>
 So far, the thrift store has raised nearly $8,000 in a month of operation. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's been very successful," Guild President Susan Ward said.STEPHANIE SIMON 
