<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: NEWPORT BEACH; CITY SUES TO BAR NUDE THEATER, TOPLESS BAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city has filed a lawsuit seeking a preliminary injunction against the 
owner of Paddy Murphy's topless bar in Santa Ana, who wants to open a similar 
bar in Newport Beach near John Wayne Airport.  
</P>
<P>
 The lawsuit filed in Orange County Superior Court seeks to stop An Nguyen from 
opening a topless bar because it will include private theaters where customers 
can watch nude dancing.Theaters are barred from that area under the local 
zoning code, said city officials. 
</P>
<P>
 On that basis, the City Council last month voted to reject Nguyen's 
application for a live entertainment permit for the establishment, which would 
be called Mermaids and would serve alcohol and food. 
</P>
<P>
 Despite that vote, Nguyen has continued renovating the business. His attorney, 
Ron Talmo, said Nguyen does indeed plan to open the club despite the city's 
objections. Talmo also said his client will challenge the city's rejection of 
the permits.  
</P>
<P>
 Talmo has maintained that city officials can't prevent the opening of Mermaids 
just because they don't want an adult entertainment business in the city. As 
long as Mermaids is in compliance with local ordinances, it has a right to do 
business, Talmo has said. 
</P>
<P>
 In a recent meeting with city officials, Nguyen has agreed not to open the 
club before the March 29 court hearing date. 
</P>
</TEXT>
