ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: GARDEN GROVE; SCHOOL DISTRICT GETS $16,728 REBATE CHECK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Garden Grove Unified School District officials say that conservation pays, and 
they have got rebate checks totaling almost $17,000 to prove it. 
</P>
<P>
 During a brief presentation earlier this month, officials described the 
district's electricity conservation efforts and how they expect to save $65,000 
a year.On top of that, they said, the district has received rebate checks from 
Southern California Edison totaling $16,728 for their cooperation in reducing 
energy consumption. 
</P>
<P>
 During the presentation, officials from Southern California Edison awarded 
plaques for each of the 10 district sites that installed energy-saving 
equipment including more efficient air conditioning and lighting. 
</P>
<P>
 Ken Calkins, assistant superintendent for administrative services, said that 
the district would use the money from the rebates and savings to pay for more 
energy conservation measures. 
</P>
<P>
 He said: "We're going to do as much of this as we can now that we know how to 
do it." JON NALICK 
