Corp. said the earnings marked a 36% improvement over the previous record of 
$32 billion, set in 1992, itself a 79% increase over the $17.9 billion earned 
in 1991.Ninety-five percent of all banks reported profits, the highest share 
since 1980, and two of every three banks reported higher profits than for 1992. 
Return on assets, a standard measure of profitability, hit 1.21%, topping 1% 
for the first time since the FDIC began operating in 1934. The loan loss total 
