<P>
 Mexico to Take Bids to Operate 16 Cargo Terminals: The government will begin 
taking the bids within two months as part of an effort to privatize the 
country's ports, according to Port Authority President Jaime Corredor. The 
concessions are for six major cargo terminals on Mexico's Pacific Coast and 10 
terminals along the Gulf Coast, Corredor told reporters at a privatization 
conference.Corredor said Mexico is targeting private international port service 
companies with either the expertise, technology or capital to operate the 
terminals. Foreign or domestic companies that have the know-how but little 
capital will have access to "enhanced credit" standing either through loan 
guarantees or other financial assistance from the Nacional Financiera, a 
development bank, said Jose Angel Gurria, the bank's chief executive. 
